# Cloud provider layer

## Required layout (fork additions)

```
packages/studio/src/providers/types.js
packages/studio/src/providers/muapi.js       # wrap/re-export; no Runware here
packages/studio/src/providers/runware.js
packages/studio/src/providerFactory.js       # DEFAULT_PROVIDER = 'muapi'
packages/studio/src/models.runware.js        # optional Runware catalog
```

New or fork-touched studio code should call `getProvider()` — not import `muapi.js` directly for generation.

## Muapi (upstream default)

- Keep submit → poll pattern in `packages/studio/src/muapi.js`.
- Do not route Runware through `app/api/api/v1/[[...path]]/route.js` (`api.muapi.ai`).

## Runware (fork)

- API: `https://api.runware.ai/v1`, auth `Authorization: Bearer`.
- Task-array JSON protocol — isolated in `runware.js` only.
- Optional proxy: `app/api/runware/**` (separate from Muapi).
- Model IDs (`runware:…`) only in `models.runware.js` or `providers/runwareModels.js`.

## models.js

On upstream merge, usually take **theirs** for `packages/studio/src/models.js`, then re-merge Runware catalog from our separate file.

## Workflows / Agents

Muapi-only until a Runware adapter exists. If user selects Runware, show a clear UI message — do not fail silently.

## Do not confuse with local inference

- **Cloud:** `muapi` | `runware` (API keys, billing).
- **Local:** `sdcpp` | `wan2gp` in `src/lib/localModels.js` / `electron/lib/wan2gpProvider.js` — do not mix with cloud provider code.

## Storage keys

- `muapi_key` (existing), `runware_api_key` (fork). Never commit keys; use env for self-host only.

## App entry auth (not in studio package)

- Dual-provider login: `components/cloudSession.js` + `StandaloneShell.js` / `ApiKeyModal.js` — separate from `providerFactory.js` (generation only).

## Logging

- Never log full API keys or `Authorization` Bearer tokens in `providers/runware.js` or API proxies (prefix-only debug at most).
